<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,366,1183]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">
The species was described as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schellenberg" authorityYear="1933" box="[573,848,763,787]" class="Malacostraca" family="Niphargidae" genus="Niphargus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="kochianus" subSpecies="pachypus">
<emphasis box="[573,848,763,787]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">N. kochianus pachypus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[932,1008,763,786]" name="France" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">France</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[1031,1254,762,787]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" refId="ref13983" refString="Schellenberg, A. (1933) Die Niphargiden der Brusseler Naturhistorischen Museum. Bulletin du Musee royal d'Histoire naturelle de Belgique, 9 (50), 1 - 8." type="journal article">Schellenberg 1933</bibRefCitation>
). The taxon is distributed in 
<collectingCountry box="[308,387,799,822]" name="France" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">France</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[398,498,798,823]" name="Belgium" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Belgium</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[509,653,798,823]" country="Luxembourg" name="Luxembourg" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">
<collectingCountry box="[509,653,798,823]" name="Luxembourg" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Luxembourg</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[709,844,798,823]" name="Netherlands" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Netherlands</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[859,1121,798,823]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" refId="ref14385" refString="Stock, J. &amp; Gledhill T. (1977) The Niphargus kochianus - group in North-Western Europe. Crustaceana, 4 (Supplement), 212 - 243." type="journal article">Stock &amp; Gledhill 1977</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[1171,1271,798,823]" name="Belgium" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Belgium</collectingCountry>
, it is restricted to karst areas, where it was collected along rivers. In newly collected material we found the species only in the localities around Liège in 
<collectingRegion box="[447,531,871,894]" country="American Samoa" name="Eastern" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Eastern</collectingRegion>
part of the country (
<figureCitation box="[767,830,870,895]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1773,1795]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1238,1752]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,1238,1752]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Distribution of N.pachypus (left) and N.puteanus (right) in Belgium. Blue circles refer to data from published sources, while red circles refer to new records published for the first time in this study." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1186541/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">Fig.4</figureCitation>
). We collected the species mainly in springs, but also caves (often in “gours” 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[426,454,906,931]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">—</emphasis>
little pools in the calcite reservoirs; see the list, App. 1). The species seems to be generally bound to small pore habitats (
<bibRefCitation box="[594,853,942,967]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" refId="ref14385" refString="Stock, J. &amp; Gledhill T. (1977) The Niphargus kochianus - group in North-Western Europe. Crustaceana, 4 (Supplement), 212 - 243." type="journal article">Stock &amp; Gledhill 1977</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,366,1183]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">
Already 
<bibRefCitation box="[300,583,978,1003]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" refId="ref14385" refString="Stock, J. &amp; Gledhill T. (1977) The Niphargus kochianus - group in North-Western Europe. Crustaceana, 4 (Supplement), 212 - 243." type="journal article">Stock &amp; Gledhill (1977)</bibRefCitation>
erected 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schellenberg" authorityYear="1933" box="[685,858,979,1003]" class="Malacostraca" family="Niphargidae" genus="Niphargus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="kochianus" subSpecies="pachypus">
<emphasis box="[685,858,979,1003]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">N. k. pachypus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from subspecies to species level, and subsequent molecular analyses suggest that the species is not related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Fišer &amp; Zagmajster &amp; Dethier, 2018" authorityName="Fišer &amp; Zagmajster &amp; Dethier" authorityYear="2018" box="[835,982,1014,1038]" class="Malacostraca" family="Niphargidae" genus="Niphargus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" sensu="stricto" species="kochianus" status="s. str.">
<emphasis box="[835,982,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">N. kochianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[991,1051,1015,1038]" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(McInnerney 
<emphasis box="[1213,1271,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">et al.</emphasis>
2014). Unlike previous species, this species shows relatedness towards niphargids from continental Europe. Phylogeography and population structure of this species was never studied, but indirect evidence from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chevreux" authorityYear="2001" box="[1098,1184,1087,1110]" class="Malacostraca" family="Niphargidae" genus="Niphargus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virei">
<emphasis box="[1098,1184,1087,1110]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">N. virei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S. Karaman" authorityYear="1932" box="[1244,1429,1086,1110]" class="Malacostraca" family="Niphargidae" genus="Niphargus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="53" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schellenbergi">
<emphasis box="[1244,1429,1086,1110]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="53">N. schellenbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, derived from similar distributional patterns (see below), suggests that some phylogeographic structure and perhaps cryptic species cannot be ruled out.
</paragraph>
